-- Bucknell Beats Lafayette to Capture Patriot Conference Title
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2013-03-14T05:38:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-14/bucknell-defeats-lafayette-to-capture-patriot-conference-title.html
Bucknell University beat Lafayette
College 64-56 to capture the Patriot Conference men’s college
basketball championship and a place in the National Collegiate
Athletic Association tournament.  Bucknell will be among the 68 teams that start the NCAA
championship on March 19.  Mike Muscala scored 20 points and Joe Willman added 14 for
the top-seeded Bison (28-5), who also beat Lafayette (19-15) two
years ago to reach the NCAA tournament. Bucknell lost to Lehigh
last year in the conference final.  Joey Ptasinski had 15 points for Lafayette.  In the Big East conference, Villanova defeated St. John’s
66-53, Syracuse beat Seton Hall 75-63, Cincinnati topped
Providence 61-44 and  Notre Dame  eliminated Rutgers 69-61 to
advance to today’s quarterfinals.  In the first round of the Big 12 conference tournament,
Texas Tech beat  West Virginia  71-69 and Texas defeated Texas
Christian 70-57 to reach the quarterfinals.  Colorado defeated Oregon State 74-68,  Arizona  State beat
Stanford 89-88 in overtime, Utah topped the University of
 Southern California  69-66 and Washington won 64-62 against
Washington State in the first round of the Pac 12 conference
tournament.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
